# MQTT Configuration (Shared across all devices)
MQTT_BROKER=broker.hivemq.com
MQTT_PORT=1883
MQTT_CLIENT_ID=ethernetip_bridge_multi_device

# Notes:
# ======
# This application now supports MULTIPLE EthernetIP devices!
# 
# Configuration is done through the Web UI:
# 1. Start the application
# 2. Open the web interface (default: http://localhost:5000)
# 3. Use the "Add New Device" form to configure multiple devices
# 
# Each device can have:
# - Unique name (e.g., PLC-1, PLC-2, Robot-Controller)
# - Different IP address/hostname
# - Different slot number
# - Different tags to monitor
# - Custom MQTT topic prefix
# - Individual poll intervals
#
# All devices share the same MQTT broker connection configured above.
#
# Example Device Configuration (via Web UI):
# -------------------------------------------
# Device 1:
#   Name: PLC-1
#   Host: 192.168.1.100
#   Slot: 0
#   Tags: Temperature,Pressure,Speed
#   MQTT Topic Prefix: factory/plc1/
#   Poll Interval: 5.0
#
# Device 2:
#   Name: Robot-Controller
#   Host: 192.168.1.101
#   Slot: 1
#   Tags: Position_X,Position_Y,Status
#   MQTT Topic Prefix: factory/robot/
#   Poll Interval: 2.0
#
# Device 3:
#   Name: Simulator
#   Host: 127.0.0.1
#   Slot: 0
#   Tags: Tag1,Tag2,Tag3
#   MQTT Topic Prefix: simulator/
#   Poll Interval: 10.0

